# Course Catalog Requirements

## 1. Data Source
- Course catalog is persisted in MySQL table **`courses`** (`server/src/db/schema/courses.sql`).
- Runtime access via `server/src/store/courseStore.js` — **not** MongoDB or client-only static arrays for production flows.
- Seed catalog (`server/src/data/courseCatalog.js`) inserts on first startup when the table is empty.

## 2. Course API
- **`GET /api/courses`** — list/search courses.
- Query params: `search`, `limit`, `featured=true`.
- Response: `{ courses: [...], total }` where each course has `id`, `title`, `description`, `category`, `stack`, `duration`, `tags`, `skills`, `image`, `featured`.

## 3. Client Consumers
- **Header search:** `client/src/modules/home/components/CourseSearch.js` — debounced (300ms) calls to `fetchCourses`.
- **Catalog grid:** `client/src/modules/home/components/PopularCoursesGrid.js` — loads from `GET /api/courses`.
- Client API helper: `client/src/shared/api/coursesApi.js`.
- Static `popularCourses.js` is fallback UI data only when the API is unavailable.

## 4. Search UX
- Search input lives in the top-right header (guest action bar and authenticated toolbar).
- Minimum 2 characters before querying.
- Results dropdown with keyboard navigation; selecting a result scrolls to `#course-card-{id}`.
- Debounce all live search requests (300ms) — do not hit the API on every keystroke.

## 5. Featured Courses
- Always surface featured programs **C1**, **C2**, and **C3** in the Popular Courses section (`featured = 1` in MySQL).

## 6. Schema Bootstrap
- Table created on server startup via `initCoursesDb()` in `server/src/index.js`.
- For inspection: MySQL MCP — see `.cursor/rules/mcp-servers.mdc`.
